{
  "texts": [
    "The two exhaust gases depending on engine type are classified depending on the presence or absence of NO and O 2 components.",
    "In detail, the gasoline exhausts contain CO, CO 2 and C 3 H 8 and diesel exhausts contain an additional NO and O 2.",
    "The information of their detailed content was shown in Supplementary Fig. 9.",
    "As we mentioned, the NO, NO 2 and CO 2, are known as oxidizing gases and the CO, C 3 H 8 are known as reducing gases.",
    "We measured the target gases using four ORSAs and plotted their eigengraphs in Fig. 5 and Supplementary Fig."
  ]
}